curry udon did not disappoint.   As other reviewers have noted the server spoke flawless English and all of the wait staff was polite and tentative.  We will be back and highly recommend this place if you're in the area.\",\"time\":1720887667,\"translated\":false},{\"author_name\":\"Paul\",\"author_url\":\"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113376130903250627758/reviews\",\"language\":\"en\",\"profile_photo_url\":\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkfy4TFdWV7r0vYhMdsCWdbnHukShlPuMMbzYrdTFV32KuElWL=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6\",\"rating\":4,\"relative_time_description\":\"a year ago\",\"text\":\"Found this place by accident.  Japanese katsu restaurant.  Their primary feature is all breaded and fried meats - fish, pork, shrimp, beef.  All fried to perfection in a very crisp and distinctively Japanese breading.  Cash, credit card and probably e-wallet payment accepted.\\n\\nA set of appetizers are served first along with hot tea.  Thinly sliced fruit, edamame, and cabbage rice along with toasted sesame seeds you could crush fresh for your salad.\\n\\nI ordered a combo that included one large, fried shrimp, fried pork cutlet, and a generous portion of fried snapper.  Obviously you have to be ok with fried food to enjoy this (they have non-fried options as well), but every once in a while it's delicious.  Cooked perfectly and tender.  Even the shrimp was not overcooked or tough.  Fortunately the shrimp was already shelled - just remove the head and the meat below is readily enjoyed.  Served with miso soup.\\n\\nFor a small additional fee you can include a drink and a dessert.  Dessert was a small flan in a rich, palm-sugary/brown-sugary sauce.  Appropriately light after a heavy meal!\\n\\nWaiter was prompt and attentive and spoke flawless English.  Highly recommended if you're in the mood for some fried food Japanese-style.  Ambiance is pleasant and very informal.\",\"time\":1705990697,\"translated\":false},{\"author_name\":\"Roman Skorzus\",\"author_url\":\"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112751163441991506780/reviews\",\"language\":\"en\",\"profile_photo_url\":\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWoAYwzjQqd5g6ga_reo49mle5Qm1gOj17RF7e_hbPHsArS_tCyaQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5\",\"rating\":4,\"relative_time_description\":\"6 years ago\",\"text\":\"A very solid Japanese kotsu restaurant with a good selection of authentic meals.\\nI had a kotsu with egg and was very very satisfied.\\nBut what I really loved was the service the staff was showing. They were very attentive and refilled tea and appetizers. They were also English speaking and the menu was in English as well.\\nAll in all, a clear recommendation to have a decent lunch or dinner.\",\"time\":1537434587,\"translated\":false},{\"author_name\":\"José Pedro Silva\",\"author_url\":\"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107391390339381554935/reviews\",\"language\":\"en\",\"profile_photo_url\":\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVFeoU1zZkPaZprkfuAX7WQEWluB25KT4qfx3OariRDEi5hJQW0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4\",\"rating\":5,\"relative_time_description\":\"8 years ago\",\"text\":\"Very good restaurant!\\nThe staff is very polite, and if you don't speak the language, you find a young man with an extremely good English, that will help you decide on the menu.\\n\\nRecommend!\",\"time\":1493989610,\"translated\":false},{\"author_name\":\"Willis Chou\",\"author_url\":\"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111611373633292475435/reviews\",\"language\":\"en\",\"profile_photo_url\":\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV21qdC-kC_pXhVC1JMeufjvkx89tOkmoOnMQhnBkVbx8nXgHJxmg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5\",\"rating\":5,\"relative_time_description\":\"2 years ago\",\"text\":\"Great food and service!  I will definitely be back again in the future!\\n\\nThe food was as delicious as I remembered!  I ordered the Tonkatsu with Black Pepper sauce and if you like the taste of black pepper, this is the order to pick! It was spicy but not burn your mouth spicy. the